Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
The user requested a series of code quality improvements and bug fixes for a Spring Boot 4.0.6 recommendation microservice (Grupo3-Recommendation). The workflow was:
   - First: Apply 5 urgent fixes (transactions, 404 handling, Redis SCAN, cache key stability, eviction prefix)
   - Second: Run a full `/code-review high` to find all remaining issues
   - Third: Apply the top 5 code review findings (JWT config, idempotency, N+1, deleteRecommendation @Transactional, exception handler)
   - Fourth: Apply 3 more findings (ResourceDTO @NotNull level, dead AuthServiceClient, unbounded findByUserId)
   - Fifth: Apply TOCTOU fix and ddl-auto → Flyway migration
   - Sixth: Fix cacheKeyPrefix recomputation (evictUserCache optimization) — led to chain of fixes for `protected` method access and `IOException` compile error
   - Seventh: Explain VS Code MSSQL extension SQL dialect false positives
   - Eighth: Run a complete test of the project (currently in progress — BLOCKED due to Flyway not running migrations)

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Spring Boot 4.0.6 + Spring Framework 7 + Hibernate 7.2.12
   - Spring Data JPA with PostgreSQL (port 5433)
   - Spring Data Redis with `StringRedisTemplate`, `RedisCacheManager`, `RedisCacheConfiguration`
   - Redis SCAN cursor (non-blocking O(1)) vs KEYS (blocking O(N))
   - `@Transactional` + `TransactionSynchronizationManager.registerSynchronization` afterCommit pattern
   - Spring Cache `@Cacheable` with custom `KeyGenerator` bean
   - `@EntityGraph(attributePaths = "resource")` to eliminate N+1 queries
   - `FetchType.LAZY` on `@ManyToOne` associations
   - Flyway 11.x with `flyway-database-postgresql` (Spring Boot 4 BOM)
   - `ddl-auto=validate` replacing `ddl-auto=update`
   - `baseline-on-migrate=true`, `baseline-version=0` for existing databases
   - `NimbusJwtDecoder` + `JwtValidators.createDefaultWithIssuer` for JWT validation
   - `AccessDeniedException` → 403, `DataIntegrityViolationException` → 409
   - TOCTOU race condition between `existsById` + `deleteById`
   - `RedisCacheConfiguration.getKeyPrefixFor(String)` (public) vs `RedisCacheManager.getDefaultCacheConfiguration()` (protected)
   - Java 21 via VS Code RedHat Java extension at `C:\Users\rafae\.vscode\extensions\redhat.java-1.54.0-win32-x64\jre\21.0.10-win32-x86_64`

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **recommendation/src/main/java/com/example/recommendation/service/RecommendationService.java**
     - Most heavily modified file. Final state:
     ```java
     @Service
     public class RecommendationService {
         static final String CACHE_NAME = "recommendations";
         private final RecommendationRepository recommendationRepository;
         private final ResourceRepository resourceRepository;
         private final StringRedisTemplate redisTemplate;
         private final String cacheKeyPrefix;  // computed once at startup

         public RecommendationService(RecommendationRepository recommendationRepository,
                                      ResourceRepository resourceRepository,
                                      StringRedisTemplate redisTemplate,
                                      RedisCacheConfiguration cacheConfiguration) {
             this.recommendationRepository = recommendationRepository;
             this.resourceRepository = resourceRepository;
             this.redisTemplate = redisTemplate;
             this.cacheKeyPrefix = cacheConfiguration.getKeyPrefixFor(CACHE_NAME);
         }

         @Transactional
         public void generateRecommendation(AssessmentTriggerDTO trigger) {
             List<Resource> resources = resourceRepository.findByCompetencyIdAndLevelOrUnclassified(
                     trigger.getCompetencyId(), trigger.getLevel());
             if (resources.isEmpty()) throw new NotFoundException(...);
             recommendationRepository.deleteByUserIdAndCompetencyId(
                     trigger.getUserId(), trigger.getCompetencyId());
             // ... saveAll recommendations ...
             Long userId = trigger.getUserId();
             TransactionSynchronizationManager.registerSynchronization(new TransactionSynchronization() {
                 @Override public void afterCommit() { evictUserCache(userId); }
             });
         }

         @Cacheable(value = CACHE_NAME, keyGenerator = "recommendationKeyGenerator")
         public List<RecommendationDTO> getUserRecommendations(Long userId, Pageable pageable) { ... }

         @Transactional
         public void deleteRecommendation(Long id) {
             Recommendation rec = recommendationRepository.findById(id)
                     .orElseThrow(() -> new NotFoundException(...));
             recommendationRepository.delete(rec);
             Long userId = rec.getUserId();
             TransactionSynchronizationManager.registerSynchronization(new TransactionSynchronization() {
                 @Override public void afterCommit() { evictUserCache(userId); }
             });
         }

         private void evictUserCache(Long userId) {
             Set<String> keys = scanKeys(cacheKeyPrefix + userId + ":*");
             if (!keys.isEmpty()) redisTemplate.delete(keys);
         }

         private Set<String> scanKeys(String pattern) {
             return redisTemplate.execute((RedisCallback<Set<String>>) connection -> {
                 Set<String> result = new HashSet<>();
                 ScanOptions opts = ScanOptions.scanOptions().match(pattern).count(200).build();
                 Cursor<byte[]> cursor = connection.keyCommands().scan(opts);
                 try {
                     while (cursor.hasNext())
                         result.add(new String(cursor.next(), StandardCharsets.UTF_8));
                 } finally {
                     try { cursor.close(); } catch (Exception ignored) {}
                 }
                 return result;
             });
         }
     }
     ```

   - **recommendation/src/main/java/com/example/recommendation/config/CacheConfig.java**
     - Split `RedisCacheConfiguration` into its own `@Bean` (named `redisCacheConfiguration`) so it can be injected into `RecommendationService`:
     ```java
     @Bean
     public RedisCacheConfiguration redisCacheConfiguration() {
         return RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
                 .entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(10))
                 .disableCachingNullValues()
                 .serializeValuesWith(
                     RedisSerializationContext.SerializationPair.fromSerializer(
                         new GenericJackson2JsonRedisSerializer()));
     }

     @Bean
     public RedisCacheManager cacheManager(RedisConnectionFactory connectionFactory,
                                           RedisCacheConfiguration redisCacheConfiguration) {
         return RedisCacheManager.builder(connectionFactory)
                 .cacheDefaults(redisCacheConfiguration).build();
     }

     @Bean("recommendationKeyGenerator")
     public KeyGenerator recommendationKeyGenerator() {
         return (target, method, params) -> {
             Long userId = (Long) params[0];
             Pageable pageable = (Pageable) params[1];
             String sortKey = StreamSupport.stream(pageable.getSort().spliterator(), false)
                 .map(o -> o.getProperty() + "_" + o.getDirection())
                 .sorted().collect(joining(","));
             return userId + ":" + pageable.getPageNumber() + ":" + pageable.getPageSize() + ":" + sortKey;
         };
     }
     ```

